analysis.title: Global Market Outlook
analysis.content: Consolidation regime persists amid volatility expansion. Current GMS metrics at 52 necessitate a cautionary stance as the VIX breaches the 20-handle, signaling an inflection in the volatility surface. While net liquidity remains robust at 5700, the stagnation in the copper-gold vector and rapid crypto sentiment decay indicate a deceleration in risk-on momentum. Credit spread compression offers diminishing returns, mandating a pivot toward defensive convexity until tariff-driven macro catalysts resolve. [ACTION: WAIT FOR PULLBACK]
